{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3012134,"name":"William","username":"WilliamB","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/w/6bbea6/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-02-24T05:11:06.186Z","cooked":"<p>I’m currently trying to program a wheeled intake that is deployed via pneumatic. I was hoping to be able to deploy and run the intake before retracting then continuing to run the motors for about a second after the deploy command is called. I initially thought to do this via a <code>Thread.sleep()</code> call but was told this would lock the robot code(even though I’m pretty sure each command call can get threaded) my idea is as follows</p>
<p>In <code>Intake</code> subsystem:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">   public void stop() {
        retract();
        Thread.sleep(1000);
        m_motor.stopMotor();
    }
</code></pre>
<p>Then schedule it as so:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">       new JoystickButton(ctl, XboxController.Button.kB.value)
            .whenPressed(() -&gt; m_intake.intake())
            .whenReleased(() -&gt; m_intake.stop());
</code></pre>
<p>Would this only cause a sleep to occur for the current command or would this hold up the entire scheduler, including stuff like driving.</p>
<p>Another way which I was sort of able to get working but ran into the issue that while it would delay as intended it wouldn’t allow the command to be rescheduled until the delay was finished(basically the delay command couldn’t be interupted)</p>
<p><code>FloorIntake</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">public class FloorIntake extends CommandBase {

    private final Intake m_intake;

    public FloorIntake(Intake intake) {
        m_intake = intake;
        addRequirements(intake);
    }

    @Override
    public void initialize() {
        m_intake.extend();
    }

    @Override
    public void execute() {
        m_intake.set(IntakeConstants.RPM);
    }

    @Override 
    public void end(boolean interrupted) {
        m_intake.retract(); 
    }

}
</code></pre>
<p>scheduled as so:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">  new JoystickButton(ctl, XboxController.Axis.kLeftTrigger.value)
            .whenPressed(m_floorLeftIntake)
            .whenReleased(new InstantCommand(() -&gt; m_leftIntake.retract())
                .andThen(new WaitCommand(1))
                .andThen(() -&gt; m_floorLeftIntake.cancel())
            );
</code></pre>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2022-02-24T05:11:06.186Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1258,"reads":280,"readers_count":279,"score":6341.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":403804,"topic_slug":"delaying-commands-in-command-based","display_username":"William","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49405,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/delaying-commands-in-command-based/403804/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3012153,"name":"Fletch","username":"Fletch1373","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fletch1373/{size}/220073_2.png","created_at":"2022-02-24T05:36:55.978Z","cooked":"<p>To my knowledge, the command scheduler is still single-threaded, so the sleep call would absolutely lock up the entire robot.</p>
