<aside class="quote no-group">
<blockquote>
<p>Another way which I was sort of able to get working but ran into the issue that while it would delay as intended it wouldn’t allow the command to be rescheduled until the delay was finished(basically the delay command couldn’t be interupted)</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>So you want to:</p>
<ol>
<li>Deploy the intake pneumatics</li>
<li>Run the intake motors</li>
<li>Wait for some amount of time (in this case a second)</li>
<li>Do something else not yet spoken of here</li>
</ol>
<p>If that assumption is true, Fletch’s advice is definitely the simplest way to go.  <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/command-groups.html#creating-command-groups" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">A sequential command group</a> is the way to go.</p>
<p>For your delay, you could either use the <em>.withTimeout()</em> decorator on your run intake motors command, or just insert a <em>WaitCommand(1)</em> in the command sequence.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2022-02-24T14:16:52.959Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":41,"reads":207,"readers_count":206,"score":246.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":403804,"topic_slug":"delaying-commands-in-command-based","display_username":"NewtonCrosby","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/command-groups.html#creating-command-groups","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Command Groups — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":50}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":29982,"username":"UnofficialForth","name":"UnofficialForth","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/unofficialforth/{size}/167902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":31346,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/delaying-commands-in-command-based/403804/4","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3012311,"name":"","username":"RCoder01","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/rcoder01/{size}/163503_2.png","created_at":"2022-02-24T15:03:58.585Z","cooked":"<p>Definitely this. If you’re trying to make complex logic built on to