,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3013030,"name":"William","username":"WilliamB","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/w/6bbea6/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-02-25T23:42:34.857Z","cooked":"<p><a href="https://github.com/rr1706/Control2022/blob/ProtoBot/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/FloorIntake.java" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">https://github.com/rr1706/Control2022/blob/ProtoBot/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/FloorIntake.java</a> does this look correct, or will this also block the command scheduler</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2022-02-25T23:42:34.857Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":133,"readers_count":132,"score":56.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":403804,"topic_slug":"delaying-commands-in-command-based","display_username":"William","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/rr1706/Control2022/blob/ProtoBot/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/FloorIntake.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":30}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":9105,"username":"Fletch1373","name":"Fletch","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fletch1373/{size}/220073_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49405,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/delaying-commands-in-command-based/403804/6","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3013063,"name":"Joe Ross","username":"Joe_Ross","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/joe_ross/{size}/37_2.png","created_at":"2022-02-26T01:08:24.592Z","cooked":"<p>I think that should work, but it hides the sequential command group logic. Why not make a sequential command group with all the steps?</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2022-02-26T01:08:24.592Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":8,"reads":121,"readers_count":120,"score":69.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":403804,"topic_slug":"delaying-commands-in-command-based","display_username":"Joe Ross","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":49405,"username":"WilliamB","name":"William","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/w/6bbea6/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":65,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/delaying-commands-in-command-based/403804/7","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3013087,"name":"William","username":"WilliamB","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/w/6bbea6/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-02-26T02:32:28.876Z","cooked":"<p>I’ve discussed a bit more with my teammates and we’ve come up with the idea of extending the SequentialCommandGroup class like so</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">package frc.robot.commands;

import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.Command;
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.SequentialCommandGroup;
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.SubsystemBase;
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.WaitCommand;

public class DelayedCommandGroup extends SequentialCommandGroup {

    /**
     * Schedule a set of commands with a delay between each except the last
     * 
     * @param delay
     *            Time to wait between each command in seconds
     * @param systems
     *            The required subsystems to hold
     * @param commands
     *            The runnables to add
     */
    public DelayedCommandGroup(int delay, Command[] commands, SubsystemBase[] systems) {
        // Use an indexed for loop here becuase we don't want to add the last command with a delay
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; commands.length - 2; i++) {
            addCommands(commands[i]);
            addCommands(new WaitCommand(delay));
        }

        addCommands(commands[commands.length - 1]);

        for (SubsystemBase system : systems) {
            addRequirements(system);
        }
    }
}
</code></pre>
